<p>Calculate the $y$ intercept of a function.</p>

\[\begin{align}
y(x) &amp;= mx + c \\
m(a) &amp;= \frac{\partial y(a)}{\partial x} \\
c &amp;= y(a) - m(a) a \\
\end{align}\]

<p>Cool, but why do we care?</p>

